name: **Dunkerron Island West**
description: Dunkerron Island West V872-691 Sheet 85 Wooded and mostly impenetrable, grazed by horses that are mainly found around the E facing bay on the NW corner at V866-690. Camping is possible where the horses graze, and also at the most attractive part of the whole island, the W end of the narrow isthmus that joins the E/W islands.
